    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      179.6,
      236.27,
      193.22
    ],
    "text": "Background and Petitioners\u2019 Case",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT,Bold",
      "Calisto MT,BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      212.72,
      526.39,
      226.34
    ],
    "text": "The 1st Petitioner is the brother-in-law of the 2nd Petitioner, and both are accomplished",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      233.51,
      526.49,
      247.13
    ],
    "text": "cyclists. On 13 December 2017, after attending a funeral, they returned to the 1st",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      254.27,
      526.19,
      267.89
    ],
    "text": "Petitioner\u2019s residence in the company of his parents, grandmother, wife, and daughter.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      275.03,
      526.2,
      288.65
    ],
    "text": "The 2nd Petitioner, who ordinarily resides in Kurunegala, stayed overnight at the same",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      295.79,
      246.47,
      309.41
    ],
    "text": "house with his wife and daughter.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      328.67,
      526.48,
      342.29
    ],
    "text": "The Petitioners allege that at approximately 9:30 a.m. on 14 December 2017, the 2nd and",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      349.43,
      526.47,
      363.05
    ],
    "text": "3rd Respondents entered the 1st Petitioner\u2019s residence and assaulted the 1st Petitioner with",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      6.960000038146973,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      370.19,
      526.19,
      383.81
    ],
    "text": "their hands and motorcycle helmets, causing injuries to his head. According to the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      390.95,
      526.47,
      404.57
    ],
    "text": "Affidavits of the 1st and 2nd Petitioners, the 3rd Respondent later apologised to the 1st",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      411.49,
      526.18,
      425.88
    ],
    "text": "Petitioner, admitting fault by stating (in Sinhala): \u201c\u0db8\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd2 \u0db8\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1, \u0dd9\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dd0\u0daf\u0dca\u0daf \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dda \u0db6\u0dd9",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT",
      "IskoolaPota",
      "___WRD_EMBED_SUB_1295"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      432.49,
      526.24,
      446.88
    ],
    "text": "\u0dd9\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dad\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d95\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc4\u0dd0\u201d (translated: \u201cBrother, forgive me; there is no need to think too",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT",
      "IskoolaPota",
      "___WRD_EMBED_SUB_1295"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      453.61,
      220.79,
      467.23
    ],
    "text": "much that the fault is ours\u201d).",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      486.37,
      526.43,
      499.99
    ],
    "text": "Shortly thereafter, a police jeep arrived with several officers. The 2nd and 3rd Respondents",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      6.960000038146973,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      507.25,
      526.44,
      520.87
    ],
    "text": "then complained to the police that the 1st and 2nd Petitioners had assaulted them with an",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      527.77,
      526.44,
      542.16
    ],
    "text": "iron rod, stating: \u201c\u0dc3\u0dbb\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0dad\u0db8\u0dba\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0db4\u0dd2\u0da7 \u0dba\u0d9a\u0da9 \u0dc0 \u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0dc4\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda\u201d (translated: \u201cSir, it was they",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT",
      "IskoolaPota",
      "___WRD_EMBED_SUB_1295"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      548.89,
      515.44,
      562.51
    ],
    "text": "who hit us with an iron rod\u201d). Consequently, the 1st and 2nd Petitioners were arrested.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      581.8,
      526.37,
      595.42
    ],
    "text": "The Petitioners further claim that, while being transported for a medical examination, the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      602.56,
      526.25,
      616.18
    ],
    "text": "police officers repeatedly instructed them to tell the Judicial Medical Officer (\u2018JMO\u2019) that",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      623.32,
      526.46,
      636.94
    ],
    "text": "they had not been assaulted and that any injuries were sustained from other causes. Out",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      644.08,
      526.22,
      657.7
    ],
    "text": "of fear, the 1st Petitioner gave a different version to the JMO. Upon their return to the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      664.84,
      526.37,
      678.46
    ],
    "text": "Marawila Police Station, the 2nd Petitioner was allegedly assaulted with a hose pipe, while",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT",
      "Calisto MT,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      6.960000038146973,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      685.84,
      430.6,
      699.46
    ],
    "text": "the 1st Petitioner was beaten on his face, stomach, and back with fists.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      718.6,
      526.18,
      732.22
    ],
    "text": "On 15 December 2017, the Petitioners were produced before the Magistrate\u2019s Court of",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      739.5,
      286.07,
      753.12
    ],
    "text": "Marawila under B-Report No. B1898/17.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      778.02,
      526.48,
      806.66
    ],
    "text": "Page 4 of 6",
    "fonts": [
      "Aptos",
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      71.96,
      526.13,
      85.58
    ],
    "text": "The Petitioners maintain that they were never informed of the reasons for their arrest at",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      92.72,
      526.35,
      106.34
    ],
    "text": "the time of apprehension, either by the 2nd and 3rd Respondents or by the other officers",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      113.48,
      526.23,
      127.1
    ],
    "text": "who arrived in the Police jeep. They contend that their arrest and subsequent detention",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      134.24,
      526.24,
      147.86
    ],
    "text": "were effected without any material or reasonable suspicion, in violation of established",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      155.12,
      526.2,
      168.74
    ],
    "text": "legal procedure, and therefore infringed their fundamental rights against arbitrary arrest",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      175.88,
      461.92,
      189.5
    ],
    "text": "and detention guaranteed under Articles 13(1) and 13(2) of the Constitution.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      208.64,
      239.99,
      222.26
    ],
    "text": "2nd and 3rd Respondents\u2019 Position",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT,Bold",
      "Calisto MT,BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      6.960000038146973,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      241.79,
      526.43,
      255.41
    ],
    "text": "The 2nd and 3rd Respondents denied the allegations in the Petition. They stated that they",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      262.55,
      526.1,
      276.17
    ],
    "text": "visited the premises on the basis of information received from informants regarding the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      283.31,
      526.47,
      296.93
    ],
    "text": "possession of illicit liquor by the 1st Petitioner. At about 10:25 a.m., they observed the 1st",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      304.19,
      526.19,
      317.81
    ],
    "text": "Petitioner entering the kitchen carrying a plastic bottle containing illicit liquor. They",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      324.95,
      526.47,
      338.57
    ],
    "text": "further asserted that the Petitioners resisted arrest, abused the officers, and that the 1st",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      345.71,
      526.35,
      359.33
    ],
    "text": "Petitioner attempted to assault the 2nd Respondent with an iron rod, causing both to fall",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      366.47,
      526.34,
      380.09
    ],
    "text": "during the ensuing struggle. As a result, the 1st Petitioner sustained minor abrasions on",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      387.23,
      526.49,
      400.85
    ],
    "text": "the back of his neck, right shoulder, and upper right arm, while the 2nd Petitioner",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      408.01,
      282.35,
      421.63
    ],
    "text": "sustained a minor abrasion on his elbow.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      440.77,
      526.31,
      454.39
    ],
    "text": "The said Respondents produced an unsigned document (marked R13) purporting to show",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      461.65,
      526.33,
      475.27
    ],
    "text": "prior arrests of the 1st Petitioner\u2019s parents for possession of illicit liquor between 2008 and",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      482.41,
      102.92,
      496.03
    ],
    "text": "2013.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      515.17,
      116.36,
      528.79
    ],
    "text": "Analysis",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT,Bold",
      "Calisto MT,BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      548.29,
      526.46,
      561.91
    ],
    "text": "The central issue before this Court is whether the arrest of the 1st and 2nd Petitioners was",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      569.08,
      526.2,
      582.7
    ],
    "text": "carried out in accordance with the procedure established by law and whether they were",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      589.84,
      322.69,
      603.46
    ],
    "text": "promptly informed of the reasons for their arrest.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      622.6,
      526.14,
      636.22
    ],
    "text": "The arrest was purportedly made in respect of an offence under Section 47 of the Excise",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      643.48,
      526.21,
      657.1
    ],
    "text": "Ordinance No. 8 of 1912, which criminalises the unlawful possession or transport of any",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      664.24,
      526.48,
      677.86
    ],
    "text": "excisable article. By Excise Notification No. 509 dated 9 February 1963, police officers are",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      685.0,
      526.3,
      698.62
    ],
    "text": "empowered to perform the duties set out in Section 35(1) of the Ordinance. That provision",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      705.76,
      526.21,
      719.38
    ],
    "text": "expressly authorises an officer to arrest without warrant any person found committing an",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      726.52,
      498.88,
      740.14
    ],
    "text": "offence punishable under Section 46 or 47 in any place other than a dwelling house.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      778.02,
      526.48,
      806.66
    ],
    "text": "Page 5 of 6",
    "fonts": [
      "Aptos",
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      71.96,
      526.4,
      85.58
    ],
    "text": "While there is no dispute that the 2nd and 3rd Respondents possessed the general authority",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      92.72,
      526.3,
      106.34
    ],
    "text": "to act under Section 35(1)1, the critical question is whether the alleged offence was",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      6.960000038146973,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      113.48,
      526.22,
      127.1
    ],
    "text": "committed in a place other than a dwelling house. The evidence placed before Court",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      134.24,
      526.4,
      147.86
    ],
    "text": "clearly establishes that the 2nd and 3rd Respondents entered the 1st Petitioner\u2019s residence",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      155.12,
      526.22,
      168.74
    ],
    "text": "and that the primary confrontation and alleged discovery of the illicit liquor occurred",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      175.88,
      526.48,
      189.5
    ],
    "text": "inside the house. The fact that the 2nd Petitioner was also staying there was not contested.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      208.64,
      526.2,
      222.26
    ],
    "text": "A reasonable inference from the evidence is that the Petitioners were allegedly found",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      229.4,
      526.25,
      243.02
    ],
    "text": "committing the offence of possessing unlawful liquor inside the dwelling house.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      250.19,
      526.18,
      263.81
    ],
    "text": "Accordingly, the arrest fell outside the scope of the power conferred by Section 35(1) of",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      270.95,
      187.07,
      284.57
    ],
    "text": "the Excise Ordinance.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      303.71,
      526.34,
      317.33
    ],
    "text": "Any subsequent alleged offences, such as using criminal force to obstruct a public servant,",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      324.59,
      526.18,
      338.21
    ],
    "text": "arose only during the attempted arrest itself. Since the initial attempt to arrest was",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      345.35,
      526.47,
      358.97
    ],
    "text": "unlawful, the Respondents could not have been acting in the discharge of a lawful public",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      366.11,
      526.37,
      379.73
    ],
    "text": "duty. Furthermore, the Affidavits of the 2nd and 3rd Respondents contain only a bare",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      386.87,
      526.16,
      400.49
    ],
    "text": "assertion that the Petitioners were informed of the reasons for arrest; they do not",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      407.65,
      526.44,
      421.27
    ],
    "text": "adequately disclose what those reasons were. This Court is therefore unable to accept the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      428.41,
      475.96,
      442.03
    ],
    "text": "Respondents\u2019 reliance on Section 32(1) of the Code of Criminal Procedure Act.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      494.41,
      128.12,
      508.03
    ],
    "text": "Conclusion",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT,Bold",
      "Calisto MT,BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      527.53,
      526.44,
      541.15
    ],
    "text": "In conclusion, I declare that the fundamental rights of the 1st and 2nd Petitioners under",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      548.29,
      526.33,
      561.91
    ],
    "text": "Article 13(1) of the Constitution have been violated due to unlawful arrest on 14 December",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      596.27,
      525.93,
      769.85
    ],
    "text": "1 35(1) Any officer of the Excise, Police, Customs, or Revenue Departments, not below such rank and subject to such restrictions as the Minister may prescribe, and any other person duly empowered, may arrest without warrant any person found committing, in any place other than a dwelling house, an offence punishable under section 46, section 47 or paragraph (a) of section 48; and may seize and detain any excisable or other article which he has reason to believe to be liable to confiscation under this Ordinance or other law for the time being in force relating to excise revenue; and may search (2) The driver of any vehicle or vessel who fails or refuses to stop or to halt such vehicle or vessel when directed to do so either verbally or by signal by an excise officer not below the rank of Inspector wearing his uniform and acting in execution of his duty, shall be guilty of an offence and shall be liable, upon conviction, to a fine not less than five thousand rupees and not exceeding twenty five thousand rupees or in default of payment of such fine to simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to two months. (3) In this section ' vehicle ' includes any carriage coach, cart, motor car, motor cycle, omnibus, lorry, bicycle, or other mechanically propelled vehicle and the ' driver ' of a vehicle includes the rider of a motor cycle or of a bicycle ; and ' signal ' includes one or more blasts of a whistle",
    "fonts": [
      "Aptos",
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      6.0,
      9.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      778.02,
      526.48,
      806.66
    ],
    "text": "Page 6 of 6",
    "fonts": [
      "Aptos",
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      71.96,
      526.25,
      85.58
    ],
    "text": "2017 by the 2nd and 3rd Respondents. This declaration shall not prejudice or affect the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      92.72,
      507.88,
      106.34
    ],
    "text": "continuation of any pending criminal proceedings against the 1st and 2nd Petitioners.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      376.51,
      213.14,
      529.48,
      226.7
    ],
    "text": "Judge of the Supreme Court",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT,Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
